---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Thumbnails Plugin">
  <h1>thumbnails</h1>
  <p class="lead">Renders a clickable thumbnail strip synced with the active slide. Thumbnails are generated from slide <code>data-src</code> or <code>img[src]</code>.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} thumbnails {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'</code></pre>

  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <pre><code>{`new Slider('#el', {
  plugins: [thumbnails({ clickable: true })],
})`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>el</code></td><td><code>string | HTMLElement</code></td><td>—</td><td>Container for thumbnails. Auto-created after slider container if omitted.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>clickable</code></td><td><code>boolean</code></td><td><code>true</code></td><td>Click thumbnails to navigate.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Image source</h2>
  <p>The plugin reads thumbnail images from:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><code>data-src</code> attribute on the slide</li>
    <li><code>src</code> of the first <code>img</code> inside the slide</li>
  </ol>
  <pre><code>{`<!-- data-src on slide -->
<div class="c--slider-a__slide" data-src="/thumb-1.jpg">...</div>

<!-- img inside slide -->
<div class="c--slider-a__slide">
  <img src="/full-1.jpg" alt="..." />
</div>`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Demo</h2>
  <p><a href="/demos/thumbnails">View thumbnails demo →</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
